data.name: AEROSIL® 130
data.description: AEROSIL® 130 is a fumed silica with a high specific surface area, making it an excellent thickening and reinforcing agent for a wide range of applications. This product is particularly well-suited for use in adhesives, coatings, and composites, as it can improve mechanical strength and increase the durability of the final product. AEROSIL® 130 is a hydrophilic fumed silica with a specific surface area of 130 m2/g.

data.name: ROHACELL® XT
data.description: ROHACELL® XT is a closed-cell rigid foam based on polymethacrylimide (PMI) chemistry that are free of CFCs and designed to meet the most extreme and demanding processing requirements. ROHACELL® XT foam is compatible with autoclave technologies, vacuum infusion, RTM, and VARTM processes.

data.name: SIPERNAT® 9000 PC
data.description: SIPERNAT® 9000 PC is composed of exceptionally sturdy, round-edged hydrated silica particles and is therefore the preferred choice for formulations with a long-lasting scrubbing effect. The large SIPERNAT® 9000 PC particles are the preferred choice for strong desquamation or as a sensory indicator when combined with smaller particles for cleaning.

data.name: BeautiFerm® Resurf L PG
data.description: BeautiFerm® Resurf L PG is a fermented ingredient carefully selected from lactic acid bacterium (LAB). It strengthens the microbial shield by promoting the growth of beneficial microbes on the skin, driven by probiotic science. This product supports a balanced and healthy skin microbiota. It comes in liquid form and is preserved with pentylene glycol.

data.name: SIPERNAT® 22 PC
data.description: SIPERNAT® 22 PC is an eco-friendly solution. As a silica with particles in the range of 120 um, it is used to replace polyethylene beads in exfoliating skincare formulations such as shower gels and facial cleansers. In addition to its scrubbing effect, its sponge-like structure can also transport liquid ingredients into the cosmetic formulation. Its microbiological quality is guaranteed through regular and stringent monitoring.

data.name: ROHACELL® WF
data.description: ROHACELL® WF is a core material with a coarse cell size that offers exceptional heat resistance and creep compression strength. It is characterized by its high temperature and compressive resistance, making it suitable for various applications, including aircraft, space, automotive, industrial, and radomes.

data.name: SIPERNAT® 50 S
data.description: SIPERNAT® 50 S is a hydrophilic, finely milled silica. Besides its application as flow aid and highly effective anticaking agent it also may serve as carrier of especially high absorptive capacity in case particle fineness is required.

data.name: ROHACELL® A
data.description: ROHACELL® A is a closed-cell rigid foam crafted from polymethacrylimide (PMI) chemistry. Notably, it is entirely devoid of CFCs, aligning with environmental considerations. Engineered with precision, ROHACELL® A foam is tailored to meet the rigorous standards of the aerospace industry. It offers versatility in aerospace applications, supporting both prepreg processing and vacuum infusion across various pressure and temperature ranges.

data.name: SK-Influx® MB
data.description: SK-Influx® is a skin-identical lipid concentrate for enhanced skin moisturization and protection. It is ideal for aging skin, dry skin and sensitive skin. SK-Influx® is a concentrated formulation, consisting of a multi-lamellar (membrane) system resembling the structure of the lipid barrier in the Stratum Corneum. It is a concentrated mix of different types of ceramides, cholesterol, free fatty acids and phytosphingosine makes it an ideal ingredient for personal care products with unique restoring capabilities.

content_blocks.html: VESTAMID® compounds are delivered dry in moisture-proof bags or in octabins. Therefore, further drying before processing is not required. The compounds will absorb moisture from the atmosphere. The amount absorbed depends on the ambient conditions of the area where they are used. During processing, a dehumidifying hopper dryer is therefore recommended. The temperature may be set at 60 to 80°C. Granules from opened or damaged bags must be dried in a desiccant type dryer for a minimum of 2 hours at 120 to 125°C for VESTAMID® at 90 to 100°C, or on trays in layers not exceeding 2 to 3 cm thickness at a tempe- rature of 120°C for VESTODUR® and 90 to 100 °C for VESTAMID® in a circulating air oven for about 5 hours. The moisture content must not exceed 0.05 % for or 0.10 % for VESTAMID®.

data.name: VESTAMID® D16
data.description: VESTAMID® D16 is a medium-viscosity Polyamide 612 compound for extrusion and injection molding applications such as monofilaments (e.g., toothbrush bristles). The material based on PA612 absorbs only small amounts of water, resulting in excellent dimensional stability of components under changing ambient humidity.

data.name: VESTAMID® D18
data.description: VESTAMID® D18 is a medium-viscosity polyamide 612 compound that is specifically designed for extrusion and injection molding processes. It is commonly used for applications such as monofilaments, including toothbrush bristles. The material exhibits low water absorption, which contributes to the exceptional dimensional stability of components even when exposed to varying ambient humidity conditions. VESTAMID® D18 is suitable for profile extrusion processing techniques.

data.name: VESTAMID® DX9303 BK E70288
data.description: VESTAMID® DX9303 BK E70288 is a PA 612 extrusion compound developed for tubing systems with higher heat resistance requirements. Its melting point is approximately 35°C higher than that of PA 11 and PA 12 compounds, allowing for higher peak temperatures during use. This compound meets the increased demands resulting from higher temperatures in the engine compartment.

data.name: VESTAMID® DX9304 BK E70238
data.description: VESTAMID® DX9304 BK E70238 is an extrusion compound specifically developed for the manufacturing of tubing systems that require higher heat resistance. With a melting point approximately 35 °C higher than PA 11 and PA 12 compounds, VESTAMID® DX9304 BK E70238 allows for elevated temperatures during use. This compound is particularly well-suited for extruding tubing systems that are exposed to high burst pressures and high service temperatures, such as hydraulic clutch lines. Thanks to its low moisture absorption, the dimensions and properties of parts remain largely unaffected by ambient conditions. Choose VESTAMID® DX9304 BK E70238 for its exceptional heat resistance, reliability, and ability to meet the demanding requirements of tubing systems.

data.name: VESTAMID® DX9330
data.description: VESTAMID® DX9330 NC is a PA 612 base polymer that does not contain any stabilizers or additives. This versatile material is suitable for both extrusion and injection molding applications. VESTAMID® DX9330 NC is primarily used in special cases where additives are not preferred or processing aids are unnecessary, such as filament extrusion. With its optimal balance of amino and carboxyl end groups, this material offers ease of processing and dyeability. PA 612 is known for its moderate water absorption, good dimensional stability, and consistent properties in varying ambient humidity conditions. VESTAMID® DX9330 NC is supplied as cylindrical granules in moisture-proof bags, ready for seamless processing. Maintain a processing temperature range of 250°C to 290°C for optimal results. Choose VESTAMID® DX9330 NC for its reliability, versatility, and ease of processing in your specialized applications.

data.name: VESTAMID® eCO LX9039 BBM100
data.description: VESTAMID® eCO LX9039 BBM100 is a unique polyamide 12 product offered by Evonik. It is an unmodified polyamide 12 with medium viscosity and does not contain any stabilizers or processing aids. This specific formulation is typically utilized in special circumstances where the absence of additives is desired or the presence of processing aids could cause interference. The "eCO" in its name reflects Evonik's commitment to reducing CO2 emissions by utilizing renewable or circular feedstocks through a mass-balance approach. VESTAMID® eCO LX9039 BBM100 provides a reliable solution for applications requiring a pure polyamide 12 material without any additional additives, catering to specific requirements in various industries.

data.name: VESTAMID® L1670
data.description: VESTAMID® L1670 is a low-viscosity polyamide 12 compound that has been specifically developed with heat and light stabilization for the extrusion of thin wire insulations and cable jacketings. Coatings made from VESTAMID® L1670 demonstrate a low coefficient of friction, which greatly facilitates the process of laying cables. This compound is well-suited for profile extrusion and wire and cable extrusion processing techniques.

data.name: VESTAMID® L1723 BK 9.7624
data.description: VESTAMID® L1723 BK 9.7624 is a low-viscosity, plasticized PA12 resin suitable for injection molding. It has been developed specifically for the production of strip clips and cable ties. The parts made from this resin maintain their dimensions in environments with varying humidity levels while possessing high tenacity, a low coefficient of friction, and good chemical resistance.

data.name: VESTAMID® L1833 BK 9.7623
data.description: VESTAMID® L1833 BK 9.7623 is a 23% glass fiber-reinforced, easily demoldable, and heat-stabilized polyamide 12 compound. This compound is specifically formulated to provide efficient production of injection molded parts with short cycle times, thanks to its excellent mold release properties. VESTAMID® L1833 BK 9.7623 is supplied as cylindrical granules, conveniently packaged in moisture-proof bags, ensuring optimal storage conditions. Experience the reliability and performance of VESTAMID® L1833 BK 9.7623 in your injection molding applications. This compound, with its glass fiber reinforcement, offers enhanced strength and rigidity, while its demolding characteristics and heat stability contribute to efficient production. Choose VESTAMID® L1833 BK 9.7623 for its exceptional properties, ease of processing, and suitability for a wide range of injection molded parts.

data.name: VESTAMID® L1930 BK 9.7503
data.description: VESTAMID® L1930 BK 9.7503 is a heat-stabilized PA 12 compound reinforced with 30% milled glass fibers. It is suitable for injection molding applications. The reinforcement provides high strength and rigidity to the moldings. Due to the low water absorption of PA 12, parts made from this compound exhibit good dimensional stability and maintain mechanical properties even with changing ambient humidity.

data.name: VESTAMID® L2123 BK 9.7507
data.description: VESTAMID® L2123 BK 9.7507 is a plasticized and high-viscosity polyamide 12 compound designed for the extrusion of flexible tubing and hoses, particularly in the automotive industry. This compound complies with DIN 73 378, Type: PA 12-PHL, for tubing. Thanks to its low moisture absorption, compounds based on PA 12 demonstrate minimal variation in properties with changing humidity. Parts made from this semi-crystalline material exhibit exceptional impact strength, a low coefficient of friction, and good chemical resistance. VESTAMID® L2123 BK 9.7507 features a high melt viscosity, optimized cold temperature impact resistance, and precise dimensional control during pipe extrusion. Supplied as cylindrical granules in moisture-proof bags, they are ready for seamless processing. Choose VESTAMID® L2123 BK 9.7507 for its reliability, high-viscosity performance, and excellent properties in your flexible tubing and hose extrusion applications.

data.name: VESTAMID® L2124
data.description: VESTAMID® L2124 NC is a plasticized, heat- and light-stabilized polyamide 12 compound specially designed for the extrusion of flexible tubing and hoses, particularly for oil and petrochemical applications. This compound conforms to DIN 73 378, Type: PA 12-PHL, for tubing. VESTAMID® L2124 NC is characterized by its high melt viscosity and excellent dimensional control during pipe extrusion. Compounds based on PA12 demonstrate minimal variation in properties with changing humidity due to their low moisture absorption. Parts made from this semi-crystalline material exhibit exceptional impact strength, a low coefficient of friction, and good chemical resistance. Choose VESTAMID® L2124 NC for its reliable performance, versatility, and exceptional properties, ensuring the durability and reliability of your flexible tubing and hose applications.

data.name: VESTAMID® L2124 BK 9.7507
data.description: VESTAMID® L2124 BK 9.7507 is a plasticized polyamide 12 compound specially formulated for the extrusion of flexible tubing and hoses in oil and petrochemical applications. This heat- and light-stabilized compound complies with DIN 73-378, Type: PA 12-PHL, for tubing. Its low moisture absorption ensures minimal variation in properties with changing humidity. Manufactured with exceptional impact strength, a low coefficient of friction, and good chemical resistance, parts made from VESTAMID® L2124 BK 9.7507 exhibit outstanding performance. With its high melt viscosity and precise dimensional control during pipe extrusion, this semi-crystalline material provides reliability and ease of processing. Supplied as cylindrical granules in moisture-proof bags, VESTAMID® L2124 BK 9.7507 is ready for seamless integration into your production process.

data.name: VESTAMID® L2140 BK 9.7504
data.description: VESTAMID® L2140 BK 9.7504 is a heat- and light-stabilized polyamide 12 compound designed for extrusion of tubing and semi-finished products such as fuel lines. The properties of this material are minimally affected by changing humidity due to its low moisture absorption. Parts made from this semi-crystalline material exhibit exceptional impact strength, a low coefficient of friction, and good chemical resistance.

data.name: VESTAMID® LX9001 BK 9.7504
data.description: VESTAMID® LX9001 BK 9.7504 is a heat-stabilized and light-resistant PA 12 compound specifically developed for the extrusion coating of steel tubes. This compound enhances the corrosion resistance of steel tubes through its exceptional impact strength, abrasion resistance, and chemical resistance. The excellent adhesion between the steel and the properly applied VESTAMID® LX9001 BK 9.7504 further contributes to this increased corrosion resistance. Additionally, VESTAMID® LX9001 BK 9.7504 offers the advantages of low water absorption, good dimensional stability, and consistent properties even in changing ambient humidity. Supplied as cylindrical pellets in moisture-proof packaging, they are ready for seamless processing. Experience the exceptional qualities of VESTAMID® LX9001 BK 9.7504 and enhance the performance and durability of steel tubes with its reliable coating solution.

data.name: VESTAMID® LX9008 BK 9.7504
data.description: VESTAMID® LX9008 BK 9.7504 is a plasticizer-free polyamide 12 compound renowned for its exceptional long-term resistance under thermal load. This compound is specifically designed for the production of flexible tubes exposed to higher temperatures, making it ideal for applications in the engine compartment of motor vehicles. When utilized as diesel fuel lines, VESTAMID® LX9008 BK 9.7504 demonstrates significant advantages over standard grades, as evident in storage tests with diesel fuel. With low moisture absorption, this material maintains the dimensions and properties of finished parts even in changing ambient conditions. However, when using VESTAMID® LX9008 BK 9.7504 for fuel lines, certain prerequisites must be considered. Experience the outstanding long-term thermal resistance and reliability of VESTAMID® LX9008 BK 9.7504 for your demanding applications.

data.name: VESTAMID® LX9013 BK 9.7507
data.description: VESTAMID® LX9013 BK 9.7507 is a plasticized polyamide 12 compound with exceptionally high long-term resistance under thermal load. It has low moisture absorption, resulting in minimal dimensional and property changes under changing ambient conditions. Extruded tubes made from VESTAMID® LX9013 BK 9.7507 are impact-resistant, even at low temperatures. This material is suitable for producing flexible tubes that are consistently exposed to higher temperatures, such as in the engine compartment of motor vehicles.

data.name: VESTAMID® LX9112 BK
data.description: VESTAMID® LX9112 BK is a heat-stabilized, conductive polyamide 12 compound specifically developed for the pore-free extrusion coating of steel tubing. It stands out from commonly used conductive extrusion compounds due to its significantly lower melt viscosity and outstanding extrusion characteristics, even in very thin coatings.

data.description: VESTAMID® MLT 7400 is a proven 5-layer tube designed specifically for fuel handling systems in the automotive industry. This innovative system features an outer layer of VESTAMID® polyamide 12, along with two barrier layers: ethylene vinyl alcohol (EVOH) as the middle layer and a fluoropolymer, EFEP NEOFLONTM, as the inner layer. VESTAMID® MLT 7400 delivers reliable performance and durability. It comes in the form of pellets or granules, allowing for easy integration into manufacturing processes. With its excellent thermal stability and resistance to oil and fuels, this tube finds extensive applications in the automotive and mobility sectors.

data.description: VESTAMID® MLT 7440 is an automotive industry-proven 5-layer tube specifically designed for fuel handling systems. This system features an outer layer of VESTAMID® polyamide 12, along with two barrier layers: ethylene vinyl alcohol (EVOH) as the middle layer and a fluoropolymer, EFEP NEOFLONTM, as the inner layer. With excellent resistance properties against alcohol-containing fuels, the MLT 7400 offers superior chemical resistance on the inner tube surface and a close-to-zero extraction level. In certain regions, antistatic properties may be required, which are fulfilled by the multilayer tubing system (MLT) 7440. Based on the same design, the MLT 7440 incorporates a conductive fluoropolymer EFEP NEOFLONTM inner layer. Experience the reliability and exceptional performance of the multilayer tubing systems (MLT) 7400 and (MLT) 7440 in fuel handling systems, ensuring superior fuel resistance and meeting the specific requirements of your automotive applications.

data.description: VESTAMID® MLT 7840 is an innovative 'low extractable' 5-layer tube designed for automotive fuel handling systems. It features high thermal stability, resistance to oil and fuels, and excellent barrier properties. It is resistant to fuel and finds applications in the automotive and mobility sectors.

data.name: VESTAMID® MLT 8000
data.description: VESTAMID® MLT 8000 is a proven 3-layer system for thermal management systems in the automotive industry. It consists of an outer layer of VESTAMID® polyamide 12 and a special polypropylene inner layer. The product offers high hydrolysis resistance against coolant liquids and urea solutions, good cold impact performance, and significant weight savings compared to less innovative concepts such as metal or rubber hoses.

data.name: VESTAMID® MLT 8EV
data.description: VESTAMID® MLT 8EV is a proven 3-layer system designed for thermal management systems in the automotive industry. It is particularly suited for battery electric vehicles (BEVs), where thermal management of the battery, E-motor, or power electronics is crucial. The VESTAMID® MLT 8EV offers a cost-effective composition for cooling line applications, meeting the specific requirements of BEVs.

data.name: VESTAMID® NRG 1001
data.description: VESTAMID® NRG 1001 is a high-viscosity, plasticized, and impact-modified PA 12 compound with heat and light stabilizers for the extrusion of flexible tubing and hoses, particularly for oil and petrochemical applications. It offers easy processing and good dimensional control during pipe extrusion, especially for large pipe diameters.

data.name: VESTAMID® NRG 2101 YE
data.description: VESTAMID® NRG 2101 YE is a high-molecular-grade PA-12 material developed by Evonik. It is designed for use in thermoplastic piping systems at higher operating pressures and larger diameters, replacing metallic piping systems in a safe and cost-effective manner. It offers superior performance characteristics.

data.name: VESTAMID® NRG 2901 BK
data.description: VESTAMID® NRG 2901 BK is a high-viscosity, heat-stabilized compound with exceptional mold release properties. It is nucleated to reduce cycle time and shrinkage of molded parts. It is commonly used for gas pipes and fittings, with a proven record of safe and reliable performance in demanding applications, including fuel lines in passenger cars, air brake tubing in trucks, and offshore applications.

data.name: VESTAMID® NRG 3001 NC
data.description: VESTAMID® NRG 3001 NC is a polyamide 12 compound specifically developed for the manufacturing of hydrocarbon transport piping systems and liners. This material offers easy processing and excellent dimensional control during pipe extrusion, particularly for large diameter pipes. VESTAMID® NRG 3001 demonstrates exceptional compatibility with hydrocarbons such as crude oil, as well as oilfield chemicals like paraffin inhibitors. As a result, it delivers high dimensional stability and maintains unaffected properties for parts in contact with these substances. Experience the reliability and performance of VESTAMID® NRG 3001 in your hydrocarbon transport applications. Choose VESTAMID® NRG 3001 for its superior properties, easy processing, and excellent dimensional control, ensuring optimal performance and durability in your piping systems and liners.

data.name: VESTAMID® NRG 5901 BK
data.description: VESTAMID® NRG 5901 BK is a high-molecular-weight PA-12 material developed by Evonik. This exceptional material offers superior performance characteristics, making it an ideal choice for expanding the use of thermoplastic piping systems. With its ability to handle higher operating pressures and larger diameters, VESTAMID® NRG 5901 BK provides a safe and cost-effective alternative to metallic piping systems. In addition to extending the operating pressure limits of thermoplastic piping systems, it offers numerous benefits and, in many cases, outperforms conventional PE piping systems. Experience the reliability, durability, and enhanced performance of VESTAMID® NRG 5901 BK in your piping applications. Choose VESTAMID® NRG 5901 BK for its superior properties and cost-effective solution, ensuring the safe and efficient operation of your thermoplastic piping systems.

data.name: VESTAMID® Terra DS16 NC
data.description: VESTAMID® Terra DS16 NC is a medium-viscosity PA 1010 basic polymer. It is semi-crystalline, which contributes to its high mechanical resistance and chemical stability. It has low water absorption and excellent dimensional stability. VESTAMID® Terra DS16 is suitable for manufacturing films with good transparency.

data.name: VESTAMID® X7167
data.description: VESTAMID® X7167 NC is a high-quality polyamide 12 (PA12) compound formulated for exceptional heat stability and flame retardancy. This compound incorporates a non-migrating flame retardant that is free of halogens and phosphorous, making it an ideal choice for interior parts in aircraft, railways, and ships. VESTAMID® X7167 NC meets the stringent requirements of FAR 25.853 or ABD 0031, ensuring compliance and safety in these demanding applications. This versatile resin can be processed through extrusion or injection molding methods. However, it is important to note that the melt temperature should not exceed 260 °C to maintain the effectiveness of the flame retardant. We recommend melt temperatures within the range of 210–230 °C for optimal performance. VESTAMID® X7167 NC is conveniently supplied as cylindrical pellets, packaged in moisture-proof bags, ready for immediate use. Trust VESTAMID® X7167 NC for reliable and flame-resistant solutions in interior component manufacturing.

data.name: VESTAMID® X7293
data.description: VESTAMID® X7293 is a plasticized polyamide 12 compound with a heat and light stabilizer for the extrusion of flexible tubing and hoses, especially for automotive applications. It is known for its easy processing and high impact strength at low temperatures.

data.name: VESTAMID® X7293 BK 9.7507
data.description: VESTAMID® X7293 BK 9.7507 is a plasticized polyamide 12 compound formulated with heat and light stabilizers for the extrusion of flexible tubing and hoses, particularly suited for automotive applications. This compound conforms to standards such as DIN 73378 (PA 12-HIPHL, Type 1), ISO/DIN 7628-1 (PA 12-HIPEHL, Type 1), and SAE J844. VESTAMID® X7293 BK 9.7507 offers easy processing and high impact strength at low temperatures. Its low moisture absorption ensures minimal variation in properties with changing humidity. Manufactured from this semicrystalline material, parts exhibit exceptional impact strength, a low coefficient of friction, and good chemical resistance. Supplied as cylindrical granules in moisture-proof bags, VESTAMID® X7293 BK 9.7507 is conveniently ready for use. Choose VESTAMID® X7293 BK 9.7507 for its reliability and superior performance in extrusion applications, ensuring excellent results for your automotive tubing and hose needs.
